title: Grateful Dead Live at Hollywood Palladium on 1972-09-09
lineage: AUD > MR > Cassette (unknown gen) > NAK DR3 > AUDACITY > CD Wave > FLAC16
description: Promised Land, Sugaree, Me & My Uncle, Bird Song, Black Throated Wind, Tennessee Jed, Mexicali Blues, Deal, Playin' In The Band, Loser, Johnny B. Goode China Cat Sunflower-> I Know You Rider, Friend Of The Devil, Jack Straw, He's Gone-> Truckin'-> The Other One, Stella Blue, El Paso, Casey Jones, Sugar Magnolia, E: One More Saturday Night

reviews.review_text: Audience Download sounds pretty sweet... not as clear as 4/29 but better than the other 72 audience recordings. But I really love the crowd sounds at this show, as opposed to the strange quiet of the German crowd on 4/29. The southern California Deadheads are clearly SO into the mix on this one. You can hear people whooping it up all over the room and it's easy to imagine the crowd ebbing and flowing, breaking into spinning vortices....
Smokin show. Suprisingly decent quality for an AUD of this era.
GREAT SHOW I WAS AT THIS SHOW WAS A GREAT SHOW,AT THE END WEIR AND JERRY CAME OUT AND PLAYED TEDDY BEARS PICNIC AND SAID THE HALF THE BAND WAS ALREADY ON THERE WAY TO T.J

Some great playing Dare I say that this Truckin -> Other One is probably better than London 5/26/72.  Jerry is completely on and employs a wide range of playing.   You need to set aside 45 minutes and listen to them go.    

I think someone should do a matrix of this show.   It would be worth the effort.
CarlaPlatt 72 was a fabulous year to see the Grateful Dead . I turned  15 that summer and attended a lot of East coast shows. Really enjoyed listening to this one today
